Section 936 entitles certain qualifying domestic corporations (the possessions corporation) to elect to claim as a possessions tax credit (the section 936 credit) against its U.S. tax liability an amount equal to that portion of its U.S. tax that is attributable to certain of its possession-source taxable income. Sec. 936(a)(1).
}
